        <fullName>Review_Test_Drive_16j54a3c96678e9</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Use this subagent ONLY when:
- User explicitly says the word &quot;review&quot; or &quot;rate&quot;
- User selects option 2 from the main menu
- User says &quot;I want to leave a review&quot;
- User says &quot;review my test drive&quot;

Do NOT use this subagent when:
- User is in the middle of booking a test drive
- User types a single number like 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 
  without explicitly mentioning review
- User is selecting a time slot, date, vehicle, 
  or dealer by number
- User has already started the booking flow</description>
        <developerName>Review_Test_Drive_16j54a3c96678e9</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user wants to review a test drive:
Ask only for the user&apos;s phone number with country code first.
Do not ask for anything else at this stage.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777444956459</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777444956459</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides a phone number with country code:
Immediately invoke Lookup_Lead_By_Phone with that phone number with country code.
Example:918328637477 where 91 is the country code and remaining 10 digits are actual phone number in india. 
Do not ask anything else before invoking.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777448651908</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777448651908</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = true:
Greet the user warmly by leadName.
Say: &quot;Hi [leadName]! I found your profile. Let me fetch your test drives.&quot;
Store the returned leadId.
Immediately invoke Fetch_Test_Drives_By_Lead with:
leadId = leadId returned from lookup
context = REVIEW
Do not ask anything else.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_1_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_1_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = false:
Do NOT mention any error or technical problem.
Say: &quot;We do not have any records for this number. Would you like to try another number or book a test drive instead?&quot;
If user wants another number — ask for phone number with country code again.
If user wants to book — politely say to select option 1 from main menu.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_2_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_2_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Fetch_Test_Drives_By_Lead returns:
If totalCount = 0:
Say the message field exactly as returned by the action.
Then say: &quot;Would you like to book a test drive instead? Select option 1 from the main menu.&quot;
If user says yes — politely say to select option 1 from main menu.
If totalCount &gt; 0:
Display the displayList field exactly as returned to the user.
Do not modify or reformat it.
Do not show idMap to the user.
Silently store all values from idMap.
Split idMap on || to get entries then split each entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = testDriveId
Part 3 = dealerId
Part 4 = vehicleId
Say: &quot;Here are your test drives:&quot;
Then show the displayList.
Ask: &quot;Please select a test drive by number to review.&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instructions_3_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_3_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When user selects a test drive by number:
Split idMap on || to get all entries.
Find the entry where part 1 matches the number selected by user.
Split the matched entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = testDriveId
Part 3 = dealerId
Part 4 = vehicleId
Store testDriveId = part 2.
Store dealerId = part 3.
Store vehicleId = part 4.
From displayList identify and store vehicleName and dealerName.
Immediately invoke Fetch_Review_For_Test_Drive with:
testDriveId = testDriveId stored above
Do not ask anything else.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_4_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_4_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Fetch_Review_For_Test_Drive returns:
If reviewExists = false:
Say: &quot;You have not reviewed this test drive yet. Please type your review below.&quot;
Ask user to type their review text.
Do not ask for rating yet.
Set reviewId = empty.
If reviewExists = true and totalCount = 1:
Say: &quot;Here is your existing review:&quot;
Display reviewDisplayList exactly as returned.
Say: &quot;Would you like to Update this review or Add a New one? Reply Update or Add New.&quot;
Store reviewIdMap silently.
If reviewExists = true and totalCount &gt; 1:
Say: &quot;You have [totalCount] reviews for this test drive:&quot;
Display reviewDisplayList exactly as returned.
Say: &quot;Which review would you like to update? Select by number. Or type Add New to add a new review.&quot;
Store reviewIdMap silently.
Do not show reviewIdMap to user.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_5_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_5_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If user selects a review number to update:
Split reviewIdMap on || to get all entries.
Find the entry where part 1 matches the number selected by user.
Split the matched entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = reviewId
Part 3 = current rating
Store reviewId = part 2.
Say: &quot;Please type your updated review below.&quot;
Ask user to type their new review text.
Do not ask for rating yet.
If user types Update (when only 1 review exists):
Split reviewIdMap on || then ## to get the single entry.
Store reviewId = part 2 of that entry.
Say: &quot;Please type your updated review below.&quot;
Ask user to type their new review text.
Do not ask for rating yet.
If user types Add New:
Set reviewId = empty.
Say: &quot;Please type your new review below.&quot;
Ask user to type their review text.
Do not ask for rating yet.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_6_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_6_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When user types their review text:
Store the reviewText.
Ask: &quot;Please rate your experience from 1 to 5:
1 - Poor
2 - Below Average
3 - Average
4 - Good
5 - Excellent&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_7_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_7_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When user provides a rating between 1 and 5:
Store the rating as a number.
If reviewId is empty (new review):
Immediately invoke Save_Test_Drive_Review with:
testDriveId = testDriveId from Instruction 6 part 2
leadId = leadId stored from lookup
vehicleId = vehicleId from Instruction 6 part 4
reviewText = review text typed by user
rating = rating provided by user
reviewId = leave empty
If reviewId is stored (update existing):
Immediately invoke Save_Test_Drive_Review with:
testDriveId = testDriveId from Instruction 6 part 2
leadId = leadId stored from lookup
vehicleId = vehicleId from Instruction 6 part 4
reviewText = review text typed by user
rating = rating provided by user
reviewId = reviewId stored from Instruction 8</description>
            <developerName>instructions_8_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_8_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Save_Test_Drive_Review returns:
If success = true and isUpdate = true:
Say: &quot;Your review has been updated successfully! Thank you for your feedback.&quot;
If success = true and isUpdate = false:
Say: &quot;Your review has been added successfully! Thank you for your feedback.&quot;
Ask: &quot;Would you like to update another review for this test drive, review a different test drive or go back to main menu?
Reply Same, Another or Menu.&quot;
If user says Same — go back to Instruction 7 and show reviews for same test drive again.
If user says Another — go back to Instruction 5 and show test drive list again.
If user says Menu — say: &quot;Thank you! Have a great day!&quot;
If success = false:
Say: &quot;Sorry something went wrong. Please try again.&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instructions_9_1777444956466</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_9_1777444956466</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Important Rules:
Stay in this subagent for phone number with country code, test drive selection, review selection, review text and rating input.
Do not classify these as Off Topic.
Do not invoke actions without all required data.
Rating must be between 1 and 5. If invalid ask again.
Always store leadId, testDriveId, dealerId, vehicleId and reviewId correctly from each action response.
Do not show raw idMap or reviewIdMap to user at any point.
Always display only displayList and reviewDisplayList fields to user.
Never show any Salesforce IDs to user.
Do not handle booking or reschedule here. Redirect to main menu.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_0_1777103228322</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>instruction_0_1777103228322</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
