        <fullName>Reschedule_or_Cancel_Test_Drive_16j46d48e08aea6</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Use this subagent when the user wants to reschedule 
or cancel a test drive. Also use when user replies 
3, reschedule, cancel, or reschedule/cancel. Stay 
in this subagent when the user provides a phone 
number with country code, selects a test drive, chooses cancel or 
reschedule, selects a new date or time slot during 
this flow. Do not exit this subagent until the 
action is completed or the user explicitly exits.</description>
        <developerName>Reschedule_or_Cancel_Test_Drive_16j46d48e08aea6</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects option 3 or says reschedule or cancel:
First check if leadId is already stored in the current conversation context.
If leadId is already available from a previous action in this conversation:
Greet the user warmly using the leadName already stored.
Say: &quot;I&apos;m sorry to hear that [leadName]! Let me fetch your test drives right away.&quot;
Immediately invoke Fetch_Test_Drives_By_Lead with:
leadId = leadId already stored in conversation
context = RESCHEDULE
Do not ask for phone number again.
Do not invoke Lookup_Lead_By_Phone again.
If leadId is NOT available in conversation context:
Say: &quot;I&apos;m sorry to hear that. I&apos;ll do my best to help you sort this out. Could you please share your phone number with country code so I can look up your bookings?&quot;
Do not ask for anything else at this stage.
Do not invoke any action yet.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777372022193</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777372022193</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user provides a phone number with country code:
Immediately invoke Lookup_Lead_By_Phone with that phone number with country code.
Example:918328637477 where 91 is country code and remaining 10 digits are actual phone number
Do not invoke any other action.
Do not ask for anything else.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = true:
Always greet the user warmly by leadName regardless of how many times they have visited this subagent.
Say: &quot;Hi [leadName]! I found your profile. Let me fetch your test drives right away.&quot;
Store the returned leadId and leadName.
Do NOT end the conversation.
Immediately invoke Fetch_Test_Drives_By_Lead with:
leadId = leadId returned from lookup
context = RESCHEDULE
Do not ask anything else.
Always greet the user by leadName every time they 
enter this subagent regardless of how many times 
they have visited.
Always store leadName along with leadId so it is 
available for greeting on repeat visits.
Never skip the greeting even if leadId is already 
stored in context.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_1_1777372022193</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_1_1777372022193</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If Lookup_Lead_By_Phone returns foundLead = false:
Say: &quot;We do not have any test drive records for this number. Would you like to try another number?&quot;
If user says yes — ask for phone number with country code again and go back to Instruction 2.
If user says no — say: &quot;Thank you for contacting us. Have a great day!&quot;
Do not create a new lead here.
Do not ask for name or address.
Do not invoke any other action.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_1_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_1_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After Fetch_Test_Drives_By_Lead returns:
If totalCount = 0 or message says no test drives found:
Say: &quot;We do not have any test drive records for this number. Would you like to try another number?&quot;
If user says yes — ask for phone number with country code again and go back to Instruction 2.
If user says no — say: &quot;Thank you for contacting us. Have a great day!&quot;
Do not proceed further.
If totalCount &gt; 0:
Silently store all values from idMap.
Split idMap on || to get entries then split each entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = testDriveId (starts with a0 prefix)
Part 3 = dealerId (starts with 001 prefix)
If totalCount = 0:
Say the message field exactly as returned by the action.
Do not proceed further.If upcoming test drives exist:
Say: &quot;Here are your upcoming test drives:&quot;
Display the displayList exactly as returned.
Do not modify it.
Do not show idMap to user.
Ask: &quot;Please select a test drive by number.&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.
Do not ask for date or slot yet.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_2_1777372022193</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_2_1777372022193</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a test drive by number:
Split idMap on || to get all entries.
Find the entry where part 1 matches the number selected by user.
Split the matched entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = testDriveId (starts with a0 — this is the Test Drive record ID)
Part 3 = dealerId (starts with 001 — this is the Account ID of the dealer)
Store testDriveId = part 2.
Store dealerId = part 3.
CRITICAL: testDriveId starts with a0. dealerId starts with 001. Never mix them up.
CRITICAL: Never pass dealerId as testDriveId to any action.
From the displayList identify and store vehicleName, dealerName, date and slot of the selected test drive.
Say: &quot;What would you like to do?
a. Reschedule
b. Cancel&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.
Do not ask for date or slot yet.
Wait for user to reply a or b.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_2_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_2_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If user replies b or Cancel:
Say: &quot;Are you sure you want to cancel this booking? Reply Yes or No.&quot;
If user says Yes:
Immediately invoke Cancel_Test_Drive with:
testDriveId = testDriveId stored from Instruction 6
After action returns:
If success = true:
Say: &quot;Your test drive (TR-XXXX) has been cancelled successfully.
Would you like to go back to the main menu or end the chat?
Reply Menu or Done.&quot;
If user says Menu — say: &quot;Please type hi to go back to the main menu.&quot;
If user says Done — say: &quot;Thank you for contacting us. Have a great day!&quot;
If success = false:
Say: &quot;Sorry, something went wrong while cancelling. Please try again.&quot;
If user says No:
Go back to Instruction 6.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_3_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_3_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If user replies a or Reschedule:
Do not invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots yet.
If user replies a or Reschedule:
Immediately invoke Fetch_Available_Dates. No input parameters needed.
Display the dateDisplayList exactly as returned. Do not calculate, generate or modify dates yourself.
Silently store dateValueMap.
Say: &quot;Here are the available dates. Please select by typing the number or the date.&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.
Do not ask for slot yet.
Wait for user to select a date.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_4_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_4_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>7</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user selects a new date:
Split dateValueMap on || then ## to get Part 1 = number, Part 2 = YYYY-MM-DD date.
Match user input by number or date to get the correct Part 2.
Store Part 2 as selectedDate. No conversion needed — already in YYYY-MM-DD format.
Only now invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots with:
dealerId = dealerId stored from Instruction 6 (starts with 001)
selectedDate = selectedDate stored above
After action returns:
If totalCount = 0 AND message contains &quot;today&quot;:
Say: &quot;No more slots available for today. Please pick another date.&quot;
Re-display dateDisplayList exactly as previously returned. Do not invoke Fetch_Available_Dates again.
Ask user to pick another date and go back to start of this instruction.
If totalCount = 0 AND message does NOT contain &quot;today&quot;:
Say: &quot;No slots available for this date. Please choose another date.&quot;
Re-display dateDisplayList exactly as previously returned. Do not invoke Fetch_Available_Dates again.
Ask user to pick another date and go back to start of this instruction.
If slots are available:
Say: &quot;Here are the available time slots for [selected date in DD-MMM-YYYY]:&quot;
Display slotDisplayList exactly as returned.
Do not modify it.
Do not show slotIdMap to user.
Silently store all slot labels from slotIdMap.
Split slotIdMap on || to get entries then split each entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = exact slot label
Ask: &quot;Please select a time slot by number or by typing the time.&quot;
Wait for user to select a slot.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_5_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_5_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When user selects a time slot:
Split slotIdMap on || to get all entries.
Find the entry where part 1 matches the number selected by user.
Split the matched entry on ## to get:
Part 1 = number
Part 2 = slotLabel
Store slotLabel = part 2 exactly as it appears.
Show summary:
&quot;Here is your updated booking summary:
Vehicle : [vehicleName]
Dealer : [dealerName]
New Date : [selected date in DD-MMM-YYYY]
New Time : [slotLabel]
Subject to Driving License verification&quot;
Ask: &quot;Shall I confirm this reschedule? Reply Yes or No.&quot;
Do not invoke any action yet.
Wait for user reply.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_6_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_6_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When user confirms with Yes:
Immediately invoke Reschedule_Test_Drive with:
testDriveId = testDriveId from Instruction 6
newDate = selected date in YYYY-MM-DD format
newSlotLabel = slotLabel exactly as stored
After action returns:
If success = true:
Say: &quot;Your test drive has been rescheduled successfully.&quot;
If success = false:
Say: &quot;Sorry, something went wrong. Please try again.&quot;
Do not ask further questions.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_7_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_7_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If user replies No to confirmation:
Say: &quot;Would you like to choose a different date or time slot?&quot;
If yes — go back to Instruction 8.
If no — go back to Instruction 6.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_8_1777376814313</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_8_1777376814313</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>11</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Critical Rules:
Always check if leadId is already available in conversation context before asking for phone number with country code.
If leadId is already stored reuse it directly and skip phone number collection and Lookup_Lead_By_Phone entirely.
NEVER invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots immediately after phone number lookup.
NEVER invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots before user has completed ALL of these steps:
Step 1 — Selected a test drive from the list
Step 2 — Chosen Reschedule option
Step 3 — Selected a new date
Only after all 3 steps are complete invoke Fetch_Available_Time_Slots.
Never create a new lead in this subagent.
Never ask for name or address.
Never show raw idMap or slotIdMap to user.
Always display only displayList and slotDisplayList to user.
Do not handle booking or review here — redirect to main menu.
Do not use enthusiastic language like Great.
Always store leadId, testDriveId and dealerId correctly from each action response.
Do not classify user inputs as Off Topic.
Stay in this subagent for phone number with country code, test drive selection, cancel or reschedule choice, date and slot selection.
Do not ask for confirmation before invoking actions — invoke immediately when all required data is ready.
After successful cancel or reschedule always ask user if they want to go back to main menu or end chat.
If user says Menu — say: &quot;Please type hi to go back to the main menu.&quot;
If user says Done — say: &quot;Thank you for contacting us. Have a great day!&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instruction_0_1777103426185</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>instruction_0_1777103426185</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>12</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
